{"lemma":"مِذْرَى","slug":"مِذْرَى","root":"ذ.ر.#","root_slug":"ذ-ر-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ذ-ر-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n13752","n13851","n13854"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%90%D8%B0%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%89"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n13752","headword_ar":"مُذْرِيٌ","root":"*rA^","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see 4, last sentence."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n13851","headword_ar":"مِذْرًى","root":"*rw and *rY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mi*oraApN","text_ar":"مِذْرَاةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A wooden implement,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a small wooden implement,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(so in one copy of the S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"several"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ex tremities"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prongs"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which one winnows"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wheat, and with which the heaps of grain are cleared"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the straw &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S) or the former word signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thing with which the wheat is carried to be winnowed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the latter, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wooden implement with which one winnows."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.)       -A2-  Also, the former word, The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extremity of the buttock:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AO, T, M, K:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mi*orawaAni","text_ar":"مِذْرَوَانِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two extremities of the two buttocks;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A'Obeyd, T, S, M, K *) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two uppermost parts of the two buttocks;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Meyd in explaining a prov. cited below;) and it has no sing.; (A'Obeyd, T, S, M, Meyd, K;) for if the sing. were"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mi*orFY","text_ar":"مِذْرًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", the dual would be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mi*orayaAni","text_ar":"مِذْرَيَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A'Obeyd, T, S, M, Meyd.) Hence, (Meyd,) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='a yanofuDu mi*orawayohi","text_ar":"جَا=ءَ يَنْفُضُ مِذْرَوَيْهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He came shaking the two extremities,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the two uppermost parts, of his buttocks"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, Meyd, K;) a prov., applied to one behaving insolently ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAgK","text_ar":"بَاغٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"), and threatening; (S, K; *) or to one threatening vainly: (Meyd, and Har p. 603:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='a yaDoribu mi*orawayohi","text_ar":"جَا=ءَ يَضْرِبُ مِذْرَوَيْهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He came striking. &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"]; a prov. also, applied to him who has come empty, not having accomplished that which he sought. (Har ubi suprà.) ―         -b2-  ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mi*orawaAni","text_ar":"مِذْرَوَانِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two sides of the head:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*aArK","text_ar":"مَذَارٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"temples of the head;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the sing. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mi*orFY","text_ar":"مِذْرًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; accord. to AA. (S.) ―         -b3-  Also, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mi*orawaAni","text_ar":"مِذْرَوَانِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two places,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a bow,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon which lies the string, in the upper portion and the lower:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, S, M, K: *) and in this sense it has no sing.: (S:) or, accord. to AA, its sing. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mi*orFY","text_ar":"مِذْرًى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","AO","T","K","Meyd"]},{"entry_id":"n13854","headword_ar":"مُذَرَّى","root":"*rw and *rY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu*ar~aApN","text_ar":"مُذَرَّاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", A sheep"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a portion of its wool left unshorn between the shoulders when the rest has been shorn."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) [See 2.]"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}